Interview with David Zhao (@itsdawei) about getting on the Forbes 30 Under 30 List 2022, what goes into creating a successful business, and why everyone should create social media content

Key Takeaway 👉  Aligned Visions in Partnership - The pandemic in 2020 brought about some dark days in business for David Zhao and his partner Haibin Yang. However, being aligned in their vision was a key factor in them taking unconventional measures to stay afloat and progress the business.
 
Catch the full #restaurantinfluencers podcast interview with host @shawnpwalchef on @entrepreneur in our bio link!

Interview with David Zhao (@itsdawei) about getting on the Forbes 30 Under 30 List 2022, what goes into creating a successful business, and why everyone should create social media content
 
Key Takeaway 👉  Everyone Should Create Content - David Zhao is not an social media influencer in the sense that many think when they hear the word. Meaning, he doesn’t get paid from brands to create content. However, he ensures that his brand and content is helpful by telling his personal story and the story of Chubby Cattle online regularly.
 
Catch the full #restaurantinfluencers podcast interview with host @shawnpwalchef on @entrepreneur in our bio link!

You may have heard of some of the restaurants that are included in David’s (@itsdawei) diversified portfolio under his F&B holding group — Chubby Cattle, The X Pot, Wagyu House, Niku X, Mikiya Shabu House and more. We’ve seen a rise in contemporary Asian American cuisine, but we all know Asian food was not considered one of the most popular cuisines in America some time ago. When David and his partners wanted to open a hot pot restaurant, they had to take a bet on themselves because they fully believed in what they were doing even if no one else did. David shares with us that no matter what it is that you want to do in your industry, you have to find your own path, build at your own pace, and roll with the punches.
